FT  05 NOV 93 / Labour widens opinion poll lead
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP STEPHENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT last night ended a dismal parliamentary year with the news
that Labour has extended its lead in the opinion polls to 22.5 percentage
points, Philip Stephens writes.
The Gallup poll, published in today's issue of The Daily Telegraph, showed
the Conservatives trailing third behind the Liberal Democrats. It puts
Labour's support at 46.5 per cent, up two points from late September. The
Liberal Democrats stood at 25.5 per cent, down 1.5 points, while the
Conservatives moved up 1 point to 24 per cent.
Mr Major saw a small rise in his personal popularity rating from 16.7 per
cent to 19.1 per cent. It still marks him out as the least popular post-war
prime minister.
