FT  05 NOV 93 / UK satellite TV producers will be urged to include majority
of European broadcasting
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR PETER BROOKE, national heritage secretary, will tell UK satellite
television operators next week to move to include a majority of European
programming in their broadcasts.
Mr Brooke gave warning of the move yesterday in the first two-yearly report
to the European Commission on the European content of UK broadcasts.
Mr Brooke will write to broadcasters asking why they have not met the
requirements. British Sky Broadcasting, a consortium in which Pearson, owner
of the Financial Times has a stake, is likely to be among those receiving
letters.
