<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR Jim Bolger, the New Zealand prime minister, yesterday wound up the
National party's campaign in the New Zealand election, in the knowledge that
the latest opinion polls show his party holding a clear lead over the main
opposition Labour party among 'decided' voters.
A TV3-Gallup poll, released last night, showed National with 42 per cent of
