FT  04 NOV 93 / International Company News: Viacom secures Paramount
financing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
VIACOM, the cable television company locked in a takeover battle for
Paramount Communications, announced yesterday it had lined up the loan
financing it needs to support its Dollars 9.5bn agreed offer for the film
and publishing group, which also faces a Dollars 9.5bn hostile offer from
QVC Network.
Both Viacom and QVC are in the throes of a cash tender offer for 51 per cent
of Paramount's shares at Dollars 80 a share. This will cost each of them
Dollars 4.8bn.
Viacom said last night its loan package, which had been 'substantially
oversubscribed, on very favourable terms', included a Dollars 3.5bn senior
unsecured revolving acquisition credit facility and a Dollars 1bn bridge
term loan.
The bridge loan would help it buy shares in the tender if regulatory matters
delayed a Dollars 1.2bn investment in Viacom by Nynex, the Baby Bell
telephone company. Viacom is also getting a Dollars 600m investment from
video rental group Blockbuster Entertainment.
QVC has already lined up around Dollars 5bn in cash, consisting of Dollars
3bn in bank loan commitments and Dollars 500m of equity investments from
four other media companies.
