<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 93 / International Company News: Restructure at FLS
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HILARY BARNES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COPENHAGEN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FLS Industries, supplier of equipment to the cement-making industry, is
being restructured. The move will increase group turnover by 18 per cent,
writes Hilary Barnes in Copenhagen.
Aalborg Portland Holding, a building materials group, is to become a part of
FLS. Turnover should rise by DKr2.2bn to DKr14.3bn (Dollars 2.09bn) on the
basis of 1992 accounts.
