FT  04 NOV 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The wool market has continued to show strength. Offerings at auction have
been fully cleared, prices have tended to move gradually higher in
Australia, and in other wool producing markets more sporadic sales have seen
sharper increases. The industry is now firmly convinced that the lowest
point of this wool market has been passed. Sales from the Australian wool
stockpile, at premium prices, have also increased. Buyers further down the
line in the industry have been more active. The AWC market indicator touched
500 cents on November 2, from an April low point of 381c/kg.
