<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 93 / International Company News: Deloitte faces Dollars 77m
damages
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A COURT in Houston, Texas, ordered Deloitte &amp; Touche, the US accounting
firm, to pay Dollars 77m in punitive damages to investors in a limited
partnership which invested in cattle, writes Richard Waters.
The accounting firm had been negligent in preparing a tax return claiming an
allowance for grazing land which the firm could not show the cattle had
actually used, the court decided. Investors in the Limited partnership had
paid Dollars 35m plus additional penalties to the US's Internal Revenue
Service after agreeing a settlement over the matter in 1991. Deloitte is
expected to appeal.
</TEXT>
