ROCHE Holding, the Swiss drugs group, confirmed it will sell its 74 per cent
owned subsidiary in India to Piramal Enterprises, AP-DJ reports from Basel.
Piramal will take over the Swiss company's interest in Roche Products, of
Bombay. The terms were not disclosed.
