FT  04 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Oceana back in the black
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE OCEANA Consolidated Company, which has interests in stockbroking and
finance, reported a pre-tax profit of Pounds 877,000 for the half year to
end-September.
The outcome compared with a deficit of Pounds 158,000 last time and was
struck on turnover up from Pounds 4.79m to Pounds 6.29m.
A maiden interim dividend of 0.5p is declared, payable from earnings of
7.28p per share (2.43p losses).
The directors said the improvement in profits reflected a continuing strong
contribution from Charles Stanley, the stockbroker, its principal
subsidiary.
Trading in the second half had opened on a firm note, the directors added,
although it was too early to predict the outcome for the full year.
