designer and manufacturer of consumer goods reported pre-tax profits more
than doubled from Pounds 26,000 to Pounds 54,000 for the first half of 1993.
It also announced the acquisition of Samco, the market leader in branded
sunglasses, for up to Pounds 2.85m, and a proposed share issue to raise
about Pounds 2m to fund the acquisition and provide increased working
capital.
Turnover for the period fell slightly to Pounds 2.48m (Pounds 2.69m).
Earnings per share worked through at 0.53p (0.06p) and the group is paying
an interim dividend of 0.5p (nil), with a forecast final of not less than
1p.
Mr Graham Webster, chairman, said the acquisition should double group
turnover, which, together with planned overhead savings, should have a
profound impact on the group's future performance.
