<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 93 / Cardiff Bay barrage approved
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE scheme to build a Pounds 152m barrage across Cardiff Bay was finally
approved by Parliament last night. Ministers cut short the last stage of
debate on legislation with a 'guillotine' timetable after five years'
scrutiny.
The barrage is designed to rejuvenate the derelict docklands area of south
Cardiff. It has been opposed on environmental grounds because it would flood
a 165-hectare freshwater wetland bird habitat.
Work is expected to start soon. The scheme will control the tidal waters of
the Taff and Ely estuaries, creating a 500-acre lake. Supporters claim it
will attract investment of about Pounds 2.5bn and create 30,000 jobs.
