<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 93 / Photo-cards 'cut credit fraud'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE USE of photographs on credit cards had cut losses through fraud by more
than 90 per cent in the five months since its introduction, the National &amp;
Provincial Building Society said yesterday.
N&amp;P, the eighth largest society, said losses on its 120,000 Visa photocards
in circulation between May and October were Pounds 9,000 compared with more
than Pounds 100,000 on a similar number of ordinary cards.
It claimed that if all UK plastic cards were issued with a laser-engraved
photograph and signature of the holder, fraud could be cut from Pounds 165m
a year to Pounds 15m. A third of its 350,000 Visa cards are now photocards.
</TEXT>
