<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 93 / Businesses in Notts set growth priorities
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT, Midlands Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MORE THAN 200 business leaders in north Nottinghamshire yesterday called for
a unified approach among local authorities and private-sector promotional
bodies to foster economic development in the area.
The call, at a conference in Rufford, Nottinghamshire, reflects concern
about the impact on the local economy of pit closures.
The conference agreed a set of priorities to create a climate for economic
development.
The first was a dialogue between financial institutions and local business:
there is concern about a shortage of venture capital.
There were also demands for improvements to the area's infrastructure,
especially east-west communications, and for more higher educational
facilities, including a university.
</TEXT>
